#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
pot2dict GUI — a desktop front end for the pot2dict binary.

Builds the command line from the same options the Rust CLI exposes,
runs it as a subprocess, and streams ONLY stderr (progress bar, spill
warnings, final stats) live into a console pane. stdout is never
captured into the log: when no --output path is set, the binary would
write the actual password dictionary to stdout, and echoing that into
a Tk Text widget would mean dumping the full plaintext password list
into the GUI's log line-by-line. Instead this GUI always ensures an
--output file path is set before launching, and discards the child's
stdout stream entirely (it should carry nothing once -o is passed).

Requires only the standard library (tkinter). Point "Binary path" at
your compiled pot2dict release binary before running.
"""

